				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\beta $$\end{document}-delayed neutron emission probability (Pn\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$_n$$\end{document}) [295]. Predictions for such quantities may vary greatly for nuclei far from stability, being also strongly influenced by specific nuclear structure properties, in particular the shape and deformation of the nucleus [296]. It is found that change in deformation as nucleons are added results in large uncertainties in the β\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
