Next to structural properties, fission barriers and fission fragment distributions play also a central role in the modeling of r-process calculations. Such information has become even more critical after the hypothesis that fission recycling could be one of the important processes responsible for the production of heavy elements in explosive scenarios, in combination with neutron capture [302, 303]. In environments with very high number of neutron capture per seed nucleus (e.g., ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
