sec.p:
The advent of arrays of Compton suppressed HPGe detectors allowed for breakthroughs in nuclear structure studies of neutron-rich fission products. In particular, the high sensitivity of arrays such as EUROBALL [18] and GAMMASPHERE [21] has been crucial to detect the large number of photons emitted by about 150 different nuclides simultaneously produced in the fission process. In this approach, the exceptional selectivity needed to assign γ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
