Techniques have been developed to perform perform g-factor measurements of excited states using spontaneous fission sources in conjunction with a large array of Ge. A first pioneering experiment was performed by Smith et al., [390] with EUROBALL, and allowed to determine a number of g factors of 2+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
