Measurements of g factors can also be performed at relativistic energies. Figure 58a shows a schematic layout of the FRS separator and RISING set-up (with a drawing of the magnet in (b)) for the GSI experimental campaign devoted to g-factor measurements of relativistic isomeric beams produced by fragmentation and 238\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
